  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Resilience Improvement of Vulnerable Extreme Riparian (RIVER)-Extension 14/16</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a continuation of earlier RIVER project.Duration ofearlier RIVER project was 31 st January, 2014. Then the project was extended for two months till 31st March, 2014 with no cost. After ending earlier RIVER project, this project has been extended from 1st April, 2014 to 31st March, 2016. 

To support marginalised small-scale producers and landless labourers, primarily women, to develop increasingly profitable and resilient livelihoodsTo support marginalised and vulnerable communities to manage key resources/adapt livelihoods strategies to respond to climate trends and other key risks
To influence national and sub-national policy &amp; practice to promote profitable and resilient livelihoods for marginalised small-scale producers &amp; landless households, especially women,</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">achieving  major, measurable and sustainable improvements in livelihoods for the most marginalised communities in countries of extreme vulnerability to climate change and poverty.</narrative>
  </description>
